						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near a well adjacent to the Śiva temple on the bank of a canal.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1567, Pārthiva, Śrāvaṇa ba. 5,</hi> corresponding to 1645 A.D., August 5, Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the local officer Nāru Abdula Vahābā Sāhebu and states that the well was constructed by Sūrpa (probably Sūrappa) son of Kōnpa (Kōnappa) of Tarigōpula.</p>						

						</summary>
